        <infon key="n">1</infon>
        <offset>0</offset>
        <text>Ecogenomic sensor reveals controls on N2-fixing microorganisms in the North Pacific Ocean
</text>
        <annotation id="T2">
          <infon key="brat-id">T2</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="44" offset="90"/>
          <text>Nitrogen-fixing microorganisms (diazotrophs)</text>
        </annotation>
      </sentence>
    </passage>
    <passage>
      <offset>90</offset>
      <infon key="type">body</infon>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>90</offset>
        <text>Nitrogen-fixing microorganisms (diazotrophs) are keystone species that reduce atmospheric dinitrogen (N2) gas to fixed nitrogen (N), thereby accounting for much of N-based new production annually in the oligotrophic North Pacific.
</text>
        <annotation id="T1">
          <infon key="brat-id">T1</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="6" offset="161"/>
          <text>reduce</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T3">
          <infon key="brat-id">T3</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="31" offset="168"/>
          <text>atmospheric dinitrogen (N2) gas</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E1">
          <infon key="brat-id">E1</infon>
          <infon key="type">Decrease</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T1" role="Decrease"/>
          <node refid="T3" role="Theme"/>
          <node refid="T2" role="Agent"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>321</offset>
        <text>However, current approaches to study N2 fixation provide relatively limited spatiotemporal sampling resolution; hence, little is known about the ecological controls on these microorganisms or the scales over which they change.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>548</offset>
        <text>In the present study, we used a drifting robotic gene sensor to obtain high-resolution data on the distributions and abundances of N2-fixing populations over small spatiotemporal scales.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>735</offset>
        <text>The resulting measurements demonstrate that concentrations of N2 fixers can be highly variable, changing in abundance by nearly three orders of magnitude in less than 2 days and 30 km.
</text>
        <annotation id="T4">
          <infon key="brat-id">T4</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="8" offset="831"/>
          <text>changing</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T5">
          <infon key="brat-id">T5</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="27" offset="779"/>
          <text>concentrations of N2 fixers</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E2">
          <infon key="brat-id">E2</infon>
          <infon key="type">Change</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T4" role="Change"/>
          <node refid="T5" role="Theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>920</offset>
        <text>Concurrent shipboard measurements and long-term time-series sampling uncovered a striking and previously unrecognized correlation between phosphate, which is undergoing long-term change in the region, and N2-fixing cyanobacterial abundances.
</text>
        <annotation id="T6">
          <infon key="brat-id">T6</infon>
          <infon key="type">Correlate</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="11" offset="1038"/>
          <text>correlation</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T7">
          <infon key="brat-id">T7</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="9" offset="1058"/>
          <text>phosphate</text>
        </annotation>
        <annotation id="T8">
          <infon key="brat-id">T8</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="35" offset="1125"/>
          <text>N2-fixing cyanobacterial abundances</text>
        </annotation>
        <relation id="E3">
          <infon key="brat-id">E3</infon>
          <infon key="type">Correlate</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">event</infon>
          <node refid="T6" role="Correlate"/>
          <node refid="T7" role="Theme"/>
          <node refid="T8" role="Co-theme"/>
        </relation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">7</infon>
        <offset>1162</offset>
        <text>These results underscore the value of high-resolution sampling and its applications for modeling the effects of global change.
</text>
      </sentence>
